cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with unconstrained text recognition, which is a computer vision task, making cs.CV the most likely sub-category. The use of deep neural networks for feature extraction and recognition also suggests the involvement of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.CL and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the efficiency and parallelizability of the proposed architecture, which could fall under cs.IR (information retrieval) or cs.AI (artificial intelligence) sub-categories.
